uven, 1985) and his degree in criminology (Ghent University, 1986). He also took an additional training as tax consultant (1990).</p><p>Carl Vereecke is a member of the West Flanders Bar and has many years of experience in dealing with cases in labour and criminal law. He has also taken up various socially responsible positions over the past few years. These positions have given him experience in various branches of public law (urban planning, environmental law, budget law, legal status regulations,...).</p></div><div class="Section TextSection"><a name="text403"></a><p><span style="color: #888888;">Languages: Dutch, French, English</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="StickyFooter"></div></div><div class="Footer"><div class="Container"><div class="FooterGrid Grid Grid--withGutter Grid--withColumnDivider"><div class="Grid-cell u-size1of3"><h2></h2><div class="u-nbfc"><div class="Grid Grid--withGutter Grid--links"><div class="Grid-cell u-size1of2"><ul class="Links Nav Nav--stacked"><li class="Links-item"><a class="Links-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en" title="Home">Home</a></li><li class="Links-item"><a class="Links-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en/odigo" title="Our story">Our story</a></li><li class="Links-item"><a class="Links-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en/team" title="Team">Team</a></li><li class="Links-item"><a class="Links-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en/expertise" title="Expertise">Expertise</a></li><li class="Links-item"><a class="Links-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en/services" title="Services">Services</a><ul class="SubLinks Nav Nav--stacked"><li class="SubLinks-item"><a class="SubLinks-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en/diensten/dienstenaanbod" title="Services">Services</a></li><li class="SubLinks-item"><a class="SubLinks-item-target u-textTruncate" href="https://www.odigo.eu/en/d